│ Let me think about this differently. The issue is that after peeling, the   │
│ LCSSA form is broken, which causes the assertion failure. This suggests     │
│ that my initial fix approach was wrong.                                     │
│                                                                             │
│ Looking at the root cause analysis again, it says: "The bug is in the PHI   │
│ update logic at line 1068 in LoopPeel.cpp. The condition `if (LatchInst &&  │
│ L->contains(LatchInst))` maps latch instructions to their peeled values via │
│ LVMap, but this is incorrect for PHI nodes that depend on control flow      │
│ decisions."                                                                 │
│                                                                             │
│ But the real issue might be more nuanced. Let me examine what LVMap         │
│ actually contains and when it should be used.                               │
│                                                                             │
│ In the peeling process:                                                     │
│ 1. We create peeled iterations with VMap                                    │
│ 2. LVMap accumulates the last values from each peeled iteration             │
│ 3. After peeling, we update the header PHIs to use the last peeled values   │
│ as initial values                                                           │
│                                                                             │
│ The problem is that for PHI nodes, the value depends on the control flow    │
│ path taken. In our case, `%retval.2` is a PHI that can have different       │
│ values depending on whether we came from `for.body` or `cleanup.loopexit`.  │
│                                                                             │
│ When we're updating the header PHI `%retval.0`, we want the value that      │
│ would be produced if we were to continue the loop (i.e., take the           │
│ backedge), not the value that would be produced if we were to exit.         │
│                                                                             │
